== English ==

=== Etymology ===

Latin ''n&#333;n&#257;g&#275;n&#257;rius'', of the number ninety; from ''nonageni'', "ninety each", from ''nonaginta'' "ninety", from ''nona-'' (akin to ''novem nine'') + ''-ginta'' (akin to ''viginti'' "twenty").

=== Noun ===

'''nonagenarian'''

# One who is between the age of 90 and 99, inclusive. One who is in his or her tenth [[decade]].

=== Adjective ===

'''nonagenarian'''

# Being between the age of 90 and 99, inclusive.
# Of or related to a nonagenarian.

